The paper deals with the Correlation Clustering problem, which is a graph partitioning problem. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also discusses algorithms for minimizing $\ell_q$ norms of the disagreements vector, which involves optimization and machine learning techniques, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with local objectives, which could fall under the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions hardness results, which could suggest that it belongs to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
